lue.\n\ncorr = sub[rain_col].corr(sub[entero_col], method='pearson')\nprint(corr if pd.notna(corr) else 'nan')", "reason": "Rewrote the script to complete the requested task end-to-end: identify Boston Harbor beaches, filter to municipalities with >90% EJ population, isolate the qualifying beach records, find the rainfall and Enterococcus columns, apply tag handling if present, compute the Pearson correlation, and print the result. Also fixed the broken merge logic that attempted to join on a nonexistent Municipality column in the testing dataset."}) [toolUseId=call_ZbS30VpAak2YLsv68ioyfmGP]
